<aside>
 <h2>Key Points:</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>&#8649; Responsive web apps are important to create a seamless experience across all device sizes.</li><br>
        <li>&#8649; As mobile device usage steadily increases, more focus is on developing responsive web apps, and native app development should be considered when appropriate.</li><br>
        <li>&#8649; Not every company/website needs a native app, so finding a balance in web strategy is important in deciding to use one over the other, or if both is appropriate.</li><br>
        <li>&#8649; Every website should start with responsive web design, at the very least their online presence will always be viewable no matter device size.</li><br>
        <li>&#8649; Pros of developing responsive web apps: cheaper, quick development and deployment, a broader audience reach by not limiting to specific operating systems, and easier/cheaper maintenance.</li><br>
   </ul> 
